Mid-month data from the central energy fund shows that motorists face further pain at the pumps this April. Automobile Association of South Africa Spokesperson Layton Beard spoke with eNCA's Gareth Edwards about the move. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Brace yourself, South Africa, the price of petrol is about to go even higher. According to the Automobile Association, you can expect record increases next month. The Central Energy Fund says current data projects fuel to reach R24-a-litre and diesel around R23,60-a-litre. READ | Budget 2022 | No increase in general fuel levy However, the AA notes that the price of oil is currently see-sawing significantly, so consumers may get some relief at the pumps. The main cause of the increase is Russia's invasion of Ukraine which sent oil prices skyrocketing to record levels.